vidis.util.graphs.graph
Interface Network

All Superinterfaces:
Graph, Serializable, WeightedGraph
All Known Implementing Classes:
NetworkImpl
public interface Network
extends WeightedGraph

The superinterface of all Networks. This interface abstracts a network as a directed, weighted graph with a source and a sink vertex.

Version:
1.0 2002-10-12
Author:
Ralf Vandenhouten

addEdge

WeightedEdge addEdge(Vertex v1,
                     Vertex v2,
                     double capacity)
                     throws Exception
Convenience method to add a WeightedEdge with a specified (non-negative) network capacity into the WeightedGraph. The default addEdge( v1, v2 ) will add a WeightedEdge with zero capacity, after which you can call setWeight() to specify the capacity.

Specified by:
addEdge in interface WeightedGraph
Returns:
The WeightedEdge that has been added.
Throws:
Exception
